SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 333
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to commend Lonnie Spivak for his honorable
and astute service to the good people of
Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to
improving the quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Lonnie Spivak is one such estimable person who evinces the greatest
integrity and probity in his professional success in the advertising, marketing, and design
industries; and
WHEREAS, a native of Nashville, Mr. Spivak is a 1987 graduate of Hillwood High School
and earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Graphic Design from Middle Tennessee State
University; and
WHEREAS, Lonnie Spivak is an active leader in his community, and his history of
political involvement includes his 2010 run for Congress and his 2015 candidacy for the
Metropolitan Council of Nashville; and
WHEREAS, additionally, Mr. Spivak was unanimously elected Chairman of the Davidson
County Republican Party in 2023, a true testament to his dedication and prowess as a
community advocate; and
WHEREAS, not only is Mr. Spivak an author of preteen and young adult literary works,
but he has held board roles with several nonprofit organizations, including the Tennessee
Higher Education Initiative, Nashville Smart, and the Slick Lawson Foundation; and
